02:37:55,959 --> 02:37:58,959
The period is not reflecting a join.

1306
02:37:58,959 --> 02:38:12,040
Essentially, think of when I say movie is a auto-ontology movies, all that I'm doing here is stating a SPARQL triple.

1307
02:38:12,040 --> 02:38:20,040
So, the movie variable here is the subject, a is the trip, is the predicate, and this is the object.

1308
02:38:20,040 --> 02:38:31,040
So, now, when I use the semicolon, what that says is I'm going to reuse that same subject on the following line, but I only need a predicate and object on the following line.

1309
02:38:31,119 --> 02:38:52,119
So, I'm basically saying get me an instance of movie that has a movie ID, which I'm going to cast to the variable ID, which has a movie title, which I'm going to cast to the variable title, and then when I put that period, that's all I'm saying is I am no longer reusing the subject.

1310
02:38:52,119 --> 02:38:57,119
The next line of code that I write is going to have a new subject.

1311
02:38:57,119 --> 02:38:59,119
